videos.headline: Penn State picks off Northwestern in the red zone
videos.description: Clayton Thorson pass is intercepted by Amani Oruwariye on the Penn State 10-yard line.

videos.headline: Thorson fumble is his second turnover of quarter
videos.description: Clayton Thorson fumbles after being sacked by Shaka Toney and the ball is recovered by Penn State's Ryan Buchholz.

videos.headline: Miserable punt gives Penn State great field position
videos.description: Hunter Niswander's 13-yard punt puts the Nittany Lions in business in Wildcats territory.

videos.headline: Trace McSorley connects with Tommy Stevens from 10 yards out to score.
videos.description: Trace McSorley connects with Tommy Stevens for 10 yards in the end zone.

videos.headline: Northwestern QB avoids safety, converts 32-yard pass
videos.description: Clayton Thorson scrambles in the end zone before finding Ben Skowronek for a great catch.

videos.headline: Fitzgerald on miscues: 'It's stuff we work on every week'
videos.description: Northwestern coach Pat Fitzgerald is ready to make adjustments in the second half and execute better.

videos.headline: Barkley jumps over pile and reaches for a TD
videos.description: Saquon Barkley leaps for a 1-yard touchdown to extend Penn State's lead.

videos.headline: Fisher tossed for targeting
videos.description: Northwestern's Paddy Fisher is ejected from the game after a late hit on Penn State's Trace McSorley.

videos.headline: Barkley slices through defenders for 53-yard TD
videos.description: After a quiet first half, Saquon Barkley rips off a huge run to extend Penn State's lead.

videos.headline: McSorley breaks through for a TD
videos.description: Trace McSorley rushes five yards for a touchdown to pad Penn State's lead over Northwestern.

videos.headline: Alviti 25-yard pass sets up Wildcat TD
videos.description: Matt Altivi rushes for a one-yard touchdown after a 25-yard completion to Jace James to put Northwestern on the board.

videos.headline: Franklin is 'enjoying this win'
videos.description: Penn State head coach James Franklin admits improvements still need to be made in the running game after a 31-7 win over Northwestern.

videos.headline: Barkley's two TDs pace Penn State
videos.description: Saquon Barkley was held in check for most of the afternoon, but mustered two second-half touchdowns to lead the Nittany Lions to a 31-7 win.
